The issue is that `tMember` doesn&#39;t have a property `avatarURL`. In your comment you say that you get the value of `tMember` by doing `message.mentions.members.first()`, however `message.mentions.members` is a collection of [GuildMembers][1]. A GuildMember doesn&#39;t have a property `avatarURL`.

However, the class [User][2] does have the property `avatarURL`. Therefor you need to fetch the member as an instance of User first. Luckily for you, the class GuildMember has a property [`.user`][3] which does just that.

So the fix for your problem is to change the parameter of the `setImage` to `tMember.user.avatarURL`, as can be seen below.

```js
if (message.content.startsWith(`${prefix}showpfp`)) {
  let embed = new Discord.RichEmbed().setTitle(tMember.displayName + &quot;&#39;s Profile Picture&quot;).setImage(tMember.user.avatarURL).setColor(&#39;#add8e6&#39;)

  message.channel.send(embed);
}
```


  [1]: https://discord.js.org/#/docs/main/stable/class/GuildMember
  [2]: https://discord.js.org/#/docs/main/stable/class/User
  [3]: https://discord.js.org/#/docs/main/stable/class/GuildMember?scrollTo=user

